    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"balanced approach\" thing but honestly that feels like a cop-out. if you had to pick one as the actual foundation for a stable society, which one is it? like, can you even have a functioning social safety net if the debt is out of control, or is debt reduction just a way to justify cutting people off from basic needs?",
