      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but if you say the safety net is the \"foundation,\" doesn't that mean people who argue for massive austerity and debt cuts are basically just ignoring the actual reality of how a society survives? it seems like their whole argument is just a way to avoid responsibility for social decay. wouldn't you agree that prioritizing debt over people is just fundamentally bad policy?",
